cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about object detection using deep learning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new training protocol based on self-paced learning, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the architecture of the Fast-RCNN model, which is a type of convolutional neural network used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a low-capacity AlexNet network, which is a type of neural network used in deep learning (cs.NE).
